Interface MolSetInterface<S extends MolSetInterface,T>

All Superinterfaces:
ACLable, Atom<S>, Buildable, Iterable<T>, Molecule<S>, SeqWareIterable<T>, Serializable, Taggable, TTLable, Versionable<S>
All Known Subinterfaces:
Group, LazyMolSet<S,T>, Plugin, Reference, ReferenceSet, TagSet
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractInMemorySet, FeatureSet, InMemoryFeatureSet, InMemoryGroup, InMemoryPlugin, InMemoryReference, InMemoryReferenceSet, InMemoryTagSet, LazyFeatureSet, MRLazyFeatureSet
public interface MolSetInterface<S extends MolSetInterface,T>
extends SeqWareIterable<T>, Molecule<S>

Abstracts out some of the semantics for interacting with each of our Set classes. Name was originally AbstractSet, but a name clash with Java's own AbstractSet lead to some hard to notice errors.
